@CBT001.text:
This file illustrates some of the work done at AGCO UK
Coventry to use TSSO from file 404 for the CBT tape to
control an MVS system running under Flex-ES.
The members start with;

TIMER - this is the main clist which drives the other
members. This is invoked by AOF processing by some message
which appears at fixed intervals.  I have two main threads
driven by this clist;

PERFORMANCE MEASUREMENT
=======================
We were moving production off an IBM Multiprise 2003 which
had an excess of MIPS and which had a good disk subsystem of
an EMC Symmetrix on four ESCON channels.  Our IMS response
times were variable and our overnight BMP jobs had very
elongated run times.  These applications are very cache
unfriendly, but the EMC box had so much cache it didn't
matter.  We started to monitor the Flex-ES cachestatistics
for our disk controllers.  Our best bet would be to scrap
the individual track caches and assign cache at the Control
Unit level.  This is then shared out by Flex-ES as demand
requires.  I continue to collect Flex-ES cache statistics,
although I now rarely bother to look at them.  The TSSO
members used for this activity are;

CONFIG - Our Flex-ES configuration file which can be tied to
the other stuff.  It illustrates our cache definitions.

CACHE - Every hour this TSSO clist runs commands on the
Flex-ES system to collect Flex-ES cachestatistics for every
disk controller defined in the config file and appends them
to a Unixware file.

FLEXJ01 - is a batch job that TIMER submits just before
midnight each day.  It takes a snapshot of Unixware memory
usage over the last 24 hours which is appended to the
cachestatistics file.  This file is then FTP'd over to a
mainframe GDG so I have a history that I can browse from
ISPF.

REPORT - is a sample output from FLEXJ01.

RESET - a clist which is called at the end of FLEJ01 to
write an end-of-file at the start of the cachestastics file
ready to collect another day's worth of data.

STORAGE MANAGEMENT
==================
Another function of TIMER is to automate various HSM
housekeeping commands such as DELVOL.
The Storage Management members are;

STORAGE - This clist monitors the non-SMS disks and switches
them from STORAGE to PRIVATE if they get too full and
vice-versa as they empty.

SYSDA - this REXX uses the VTOC command off the CBT tape to
monitor allocations on a few disks that I called SYSDA.

@DOC.text:
This file illustrates some of the work done at AGCO UK Coventry to use
the Public Domain console automation tool TSSO from file 404 for the CBT
tape (http://cbttape.org/) to control an MVS system running under
Flex-ES.  Our reseller, T3 Technologies UK have been an invaluable
source of help, inspiration and guidance.  We would appreciate any input
from any other source, contact me by e-mail at;

davecartwright@uk.agcocorp.com


The members start with;
TIMER - this is the main clist which drives the other members. This is
invoked by AOF processing by some message which appears at fixed
intervals.  In our case we use an IMS response to another automation
tool, MainView from BMC which causes a specific message (it doesn't
matter which one here) to be issued every 15 minutes. It would be easy
to set up say a JES2 automatic command to generate messages at set
intervals.  I use this clist which is under my control rather than our
scheduling package (CA-7) which is not.
I have two main threads driven by this clist;

PERFORMANCE MEASUREMENT
=======================
When first installed we had some performance problems with our Flex-ES
system.  The configuration had been set up by T3 to our specification
to include a second instance but they left a lot of the details to
default.  This is normally fine for a Development environment, but we
were moving production off an IBM Multiprise 2003 which had an excess of
MIPS and which had a good disk subsystem of an EMC Symmetrix on four
ESCON channels.  Our IMS response times were variable and our overnight
BMP jobs had very elongated run times.  These applications are very
cache unfriendly, but the EMC box had so much cache it didn't matter.
As a first fix T3 helped us set up large cache allocations on selected
disks, this certainly improved things a lot.  We started to monitor
the Flex-ES cachestatistics for our disk controllers. We saw that
sometimes our cache-favoured disks were lightly used while other
normally quiescent volumes had bursts of activity.  We did not want to
tie-up large amounts of memory giving every disk a large cache when most
of the time it would not be used.  Reading the Flex-ES Resource Language
Reference Guide showed that our best bet would be to scrap the
individual track caches and assign cache at the Control Unit level.
This is then shared out by Flex-ES as demand requires. The benefits of
this approach were enormous, IMS response time not only improved, but it
became much more consistent and that was what our Users really wanted.
Overnight BMP jobs benefited as well, but they really got the most boost
from Application Tuning. Jobs came down from hours to minutes when the
Analysts looked at what had grown up over the years and what was really
required.  Some jobs were changed to unload the database, process the
flat file and then reload, which was quicker than random updates on a
huge database.  Some jobs were rewritten completely.
I continue to collect Flex-ES cache statistics, although I now rarely
bother to look at them.   The TSSO members used for this activity are;

CONFIG - Not TSSO, this is our Flex-ES configuration file which can be
tied to the other stuff.  This has grown up from the first install of
our Flex-ES system and needs to be tidied up.  We plan to resurrect the
second instance soon and will rebuild this file at that time.  We
certainly do not hold it up as a model of clarity, but it illustrates
our cache definitions.

CACHE - Every hour this TSSO clist runs commands on the Flex-ES system
to collect Flex-ES cachestatistics for every disk controller defined in
the config file and appends them to a Unixware file.

FLEXJ01 - is a batch job that TIMER submits just before midnight each
day.  It takes a snapshot of Unixware memory usage over the last 24
hours which is appended to the cachestatistics file. This file is then
FTP'd over to a mainframe GDG so I have a history that I can browse from
ISPF.

REPORT - is a sample output from FLEXJ01.

RESET - a clist which is called at the end of FLEJ01 to write an
end-of-file at the start of the cachestastics file ready to collect
another day's worth of data.

STORAGE MANAGEMENT
==================
Another function of TIMER is to automate various HSM housekeeping
commands such as DELVOL. It submits jobs to produce overviews of disk
usage on Fridays so I can decide whether to run defrag jobs before the
weekend. These jobs are not included here, they are simple executions of
MAP3380 and MAP3390 from file 172 of the CBT tape.
The Storage Management members are;

STORAGE - This clist monitors the non-SMS disks and switches them from
STORAGE to PRIVATE if they get too full and vice-versa as they empty.
This function uses SM80, a cut-down version of MAP3380 that I believe is
also in file 172.

SYSDA - Before we installed HSM we ran DMS, which would monitor specific
disks and delete certain files from them daily. The Users insisted that
this function was essential, they could not be asked to delete their own
files created on UNIT=SYSDA. After much grumbling I wrote this REXX to
use the VTOC command off the CBT tape to monitor a few disks that I
called SYSDA.

CACHE.text:
PROC 0 DEBUG
 /*                                                                  */
 /*      PDSDOC *TSSO CLIST TO RECORD FLEXES CACHE...................*/
 /*                                                                  */
  IF &DEBUG = DEBUG THEN CONTROL MSG LIST CONLIST SYMLIST FLUSH ASIS
                    ELSE CONTROL NOMSG NOLIST FLUSH ASIS
 /*                                                                  */
 /* HERE IS REXEC CODE TO PERFORM FLEXES FUNCTIONS ON SERVER         */
 /*                                                                  */
 REXEC -l flexes -p abcdef1 180.7.16.36 echo  +
        &SYSDATE &SYSTIME >> /scratch3/cache.txt
 REXEC -l flexes -p abcdef1 180.7.16.36 echo "d +
        ckdcachestats a00 >> /scratch3/cache.txt" | +
        /usr/flexes/bin/flexescli localhost tserver1
 REXEC -l flexes -p abcdef1 180.7.16.36 echo "d +
        ckdcachestats a20 >> /scratch3/cache.txt" | +
        /usr/flexes/bin/flexescli localhost tserver1
 REXEC -l flexes -p abcdef1 180.7.16.36 echo "d +
        ckdcachestats a40 >> /scratch3/cache.txt" | +
        /usr/flexes/bin/flexescli localhost tserver1
  SET RD1 = &LASTCC
  IF &RD1 NE 0 THEN OSWTO FLEX HAD RD1 &RD1
 REXEC -l flexes -p abcdef1 180.7.16.36 echo "d +
        ckdcachestats a60 >> /scratch3/cache.txt" | +
        /usr/flexes/bin/flexescli localhost tserver1
  SET RD2 = &LASTCC
  IF &RD2 NE 0 THEN OSWTO FLEX HAD RD2 &RD2
 REXEC -l flexes -p abcdef1 180.7.16.36 echo "d +
        cachestats >> /scratch3/cache.txt" | +
        /usr/flexes/bin/flexescli localhost tserver1
  SET RD3 = &LASTCC
  IF &RD3 NE 0 THEN OSWTO FLEX HAD RD3 &RD3
 /*                                                                  */
 REXEC -l flexes -p abcdef1 180.7.16.36 echo clear +
        ckdcachestats a00  | +
        /usr/flexes/bin/flexescli localhost tserver1
 REXEC -l flexes -p abcdef1 180.7.16.36 echo clear +
        ckdcachestats a20  | +
        /usr/flexes/bin/flexescli localhost tserver1
 REXEC -l flexes -p abcdef1 180.7.16.36 echo clear +
        ckdcachestats a40  | +
        /usr/flexes/bin/flexescli localhost tserver1
  SET RC1 = &LASTCC
  IF &RC1 NE 0 THEN OSWTO FLEX HAD RC1 &RC3
 REXEC -l flexes -p abcdef1 180.7.16.36 echo clear +
        ckdcachestats a60  | +
        /usr/flexes/bin/flexescli localhost tserver1
  SET RC2 = &LASTCC
  IF &RC2 NE 0 THEN OSWTO FLEX HAD RC2 &RC3
 REXEC -l flexes -p abcdef1 180.7.16.36 echo clear +
        cachestats | +
        /usr/flexes/bin/flexescli localhost tserver1
  SET RC3 = &LASTCC
  IF &RC3 NE 0 THEN OSWTO FLEX HAD RC3 &RC3
 /*                                                                  */
  EXIT CODE(0)
 /*                                                                  */

# ______________ - tServer Definitions
#
# 12Nov04 DHC  SPG00053 - remove maxwritesize from faketape controller
# 18Apr04 DHC Increase trackcachesize 3000 -> 7500, add SMARTSID
# 14Mar03 DHC. Permanent 29Mip license. Remove disk cache, move to CU. Rename co
# 20Feb04 DHC Multi-processor 29MIPS, move some disks to T2, increase cache
# 03Feb04 DHC Add 3480 tapes and controllers for FakeTape.
# 16Dec03 DHC put copper tapes on T2
# 11Dec03 DHC Change tape addresses to have 380 on B&T channel
# 15Jan04 DA  Add SCSI tapes, SDLT etc
# 19Jan04 AJP Chg printers to 02E, 02F ; rationalise channel path numbers;
#  remove static FakeTape and ctapex assigns (now in/usr/flexes/tserver1.ipl)
# 19Jan04 AJP NOTE! /scratch (t1) now renamed to /scratch1
#
# AGCO, COVENTRY, UK : tServer ALL Systems Configuration - MVS/390 2.10
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Note:
# SDLT     =  ctape1
# 3490-1   =  ctape2 (top left)
# 3490-2   =  ctape3 (top right)
# 3490-3   =  ctape4 (bottom left)
# 3490-4   =  ctape5 (bottom right)
# DAT      =  ctape6
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
system tserver1:
#
# Production MVS/390 2.10
#

#  memsize(524288)               # 512M x 1024    (No PCA)
   memsize(507904)               # 512M x .97 = 496 x 1024 (Max with PCA)
   cachesize(4096)               # 4096K CPU cache
   tracesize(256)                # debugger trace limit (4K entries)
   instset(390)                  # CPU mode

#   cpu(0) dedicated		# CPU with CPU address 0 (dedicated if only instance)
   cpu(0)			# CPU with CPU address 0 (allows instances to share)
   cpu(1)			# CPU with CPU address 1 (allows instances to share)

   channel(0) local		# channel 0 a local channel

#  cu devad(0x370,16)  path(0) resource(t13490a)	# IBM 3490-F01 SCSI Tape
   cu devad(0x390,16)  path(0) resource(t13490b)	# 3490 including Fake Tapes
   cu devad(0x480,16)  path(0) resource(t13480a)        # 3480 for FakeTape
   cu devad(0x400,32)  path(0) resource(t13274a)	# Console + Local Terms
   cu devad(0x580,3)   path(0) resource(t13274b)	# One-pack console + 2 TSO
   cu devad(0x200,32)  path(0) resource(t13990a)	# 3990 control unit
   cu devad(0x220,32)  path(0) resource(t13990b)	# 3990 control unit
   cu devad(0xA00,32)  path(0) resource(t13990c)	# 3990 control unit
   cu devad(0xA20,22)  path(0) resource(t13990d)	# 3990 control unit
   cu devad(0xA36,10)  path(0) resource(t13990f)	# 3880 control unit
   cu devad(0xA40,32)  path(0) resource(t13990g)	# 3880 control unit
   cu devad(0xA60,32)  path(0) resource(t13990h)	# 3880 control unit
   cu devad(0xA80,10)  path(0) resource(t13990i)	# 3880 control unit
   cu devad(0xA8A,06)  path(0) resource(t13990e)	# 3990 control unit
#   cu devad(0xE60,2)   path(0) resource(t13172b)	# 3172 For TCP/IP

   channel(1) blockmux pcach0			# Parallel Channel Adapter #A/1
   cu devad(0x3744,1)  path(1) unitadd(0x00) streaming(30)	# 3745 FEP

   channel(2) blockmux pcach1			# Parallel Channel Adapter #B/2
   cu devad(0x002e,2)   path(2) unitadd(0x2e) interlocked	# 3211 printer

   channel(3) blockmux pcach2			# Parallel Channel Adapter #C/3
   cu devad(0x380,16)  path(3) unitadd(0x80) streaming(45)	# 3490 tapes

   channel(4) localosa				# channel 2 local OSA emulation
   cu devad(0x700,2)    path(4) resource(t1osa)		# Emulated osa over TR
   cu devad(0x70A,1)    path(4) resource(t1osasna)	# Emulated SNA OSA over TR

end tserver1


system tserver2:
#
# Test MVS/390 2.10 ? (included here for illustration purposes)
#

#   memsize(524288)               # 512M x 1024    (No PCA)
   memsize(102400)               #  low enough to fit
   cachesize(4096)               # 4096K CPU cache
   tracesize(256)                # debugger trace limit (4K entries)
   instset(390)                  # 390 CPU

#   cpu(0) dedicated		# CPU with CPU address 0 (dedicated if only instance)
   cpu(0)			# CPU with CPU address 0 (allows instances to share)

   channel(0) local		# channel 0 a local channel

   cu devad(0x370,16)  path(0) resource(t23490a)	# IBM 3490-F01 SCSI Tape
   cu devad(0x390,16)  path(0) resource(t23490b)	# 3490 DAT + Fake Tapes
   cu devad(0x480,16)  path(0) resource(t23480a)        # 3480 for FakeTape
   cu devad(0x400,32)  path(0) resource(t23274a)	# Console + Local Terms
#   cu devad(0x580,3)   path(0) resource(t23274b)	# One-pack console + 2 TSO
   cu devad(0x200,23)  path(0) resource(t23990a)	# 3990 control unit (3390-3)
   cu devad(0xA8A,10)  path(0) resource(t23990b)	# 3990 control unit (3390-1)
   cu devad(0xA36,09)  path(0) resource(t23880a)	# 3880 control unit (3380-K)

   channel(1) localosa				# channel 1 local OSA emulation
   cu devad(0x700,2)   path(1) resource(t2osa)		# Emulated osa over TR
   cu devad(0x70A,1)   path(1) resource(t2osasna)	# Emulated SNA OSA over TR

#  channel(4) blockmux pcach2                            # copper tapes
#  cu devad(0x380,16) path(4) unitadd(0x80) streaming(45) # 380-38F


end tserver2




#
# Resource configuration
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------

resources tserver:

tserver1: memory		# Block of Memory for main CPU
   512				# Max with PCA card
   end tserver1

t1osa: cu osaTR			# Virtual OSA on Token Ring
   interface local(1)
   options 'adapternumber=0'    # T/R
   device(00) osa /dev/net1	# Ethernet Adapter (#1 of 2)
   device(01) osa OFFLINE	# Reserved
   end t1osa

t1osasna: cu osasnaTR		# Virtual OSA SNA on TR
   interface local(1)
   options 'adapternumber=1'	# T/R
   device(00) osasna /dev/net1	# OSA SNA (#1 of 2)
   end t1osasna

t2osa: cu osaTR			# Virtual OSA on Ethernet
   interface local(1)
   options 'adapternumber=0'    # T/R
   device(00) osa /dev/net2	# Ethernet Adapter (#2 of 2)
#   device(00) osa OFFLINE	# Assigned in tserver2.ipl # Ethernet Adapter (#2 of
   device(01) osa OFFLINE	# Reserved
   end t2osa

t2osasna: cu osasnaTR		# Virtual OSA SNA on TR
   interface local(1)
   options 'adapternumber=1'	# T/R
   device(00) osasna /dev/net2	# OSA SNA (#2 of 2)
#   device(00) osasna OFFLINE	# Assigned in tserver2.ipl # OSA SNA (#2 of 2)
   end t2osasna

t13274a: cu 3274                # Terminal Controller (400-41F)

STORAGE.text:
/* REXX                                                               */
/*                                                                    */
/*       PDSDOC *EXEC TO VARY DISKS PRIVATE/PUBLIC BASED ON FULLNESS. */
/*                                                                    */
/*                                                                    */
/*                                                                    */
 TRACE N
 NUMERIC DIGITS 12
 "DELETE 'CSOFT.SM80.DATA'"
 "ALLOC FI(SM80OUT) SPACE(1 1) TRACKS NEW CATALOG DA('CSOFT.SM80.DATA')",
        "RECFM(F B) LRECL(33) BLKSIZE(0) UNIT(DISK)"
 "CALL *(SM80)"
 "EXECIO * DISKR SM80OUT (STEM LINE. FINIS"
  do i = 1 to line.0
   PARSE var line.i cuu volser ccyl ctrk cxtnt cpct flag
   stg = RIGHT(flag,1)
   pref = LEFT(volser,1)
/*                                                                    */
   SELECT
    WHEN pref = B THEN DO
    low = 10
    ok = 15                           /* do not reduce  */
    call fillit
    end
    WHEN pref = V THEN DO
     SELECT
        WHEN volser = VCA014 THEN DO
        low = 80
        ok = 82
        call fillit
        END
        WHEN volser = VXW002 THEN DO
        low = 98
        ok = 99
        call fillit
        END
        WHEN volser = VXW003 THEN DO
        low = 35
        ok = 40
        call fillit
        END
        WHEN volser = VXW004 THEN DO
        low = 35
        ok = 40
        call fillit
        END
        WHEN volser = VCC001 THEN ITERATE
        WHEN volser = VCC002 THEN ITERATE
        OTHERWISE DO
        low = 10
        ok = 15                  /* do not reduce  */
        call fillit
        END
     END
    end
   OTHERWISE
   END
/*                                                                    */
  end
  "FREE FI(SM80OUT)"
  EXIT
/**********************************************************************/
/*       subroutine to check disk fullness                            */
/**********************************************************************/
fillit:
 SELECT
  WHEN stg = S then do
   if cpct <= low then do
     "OSCMD  mount "cuu",vol=(sl,"volser"),use=private"
/*   "OSPAUSE 1"                                                      */
     end
   end
  OTHERWISE
   if cpct >= ok then do
     "OSCMD  mount "cuu",vol=(sl,"volser"),use=storage"
/*   "OSPAUSE 1"                                                      */
     end
  END
 RETURN
/*                                                                    */
/*                                                                    */

TIMER.text:
PROC 0 DEBUG

 /*                                                                  */
 /*      PDSDOC *TSSO CLIST TO EXECUTE FUNCTIONS AT CERTAIN TIMES....*/
 /*                                                                  */
 /* 26NOV04 DHC PRUNED OUT TEST IMAGE SETUP WORK                     */
 /* 14OCT04 DHC SET VALUE FOR CMDRESP                                */
 /* 07FEB03 DHC ENTIRELY RESTRUCTURED BY DAY                         */
 /*                                                                  */

  IF &DEBUG = DEBUG THEN CONTROL  MSG LIST CONLIST SYMLIST FLUSH
                    ELSE CONTROL  NOMSG NOLIST FLUSH
 /*                                                                  */
  SET HOURS = &SUBSTR(1:2,&SYSSTIME)
  SET MINS  = &SUBSTR(4:5,&SYSSTIME)
  DAYOWEEK
  SET DAYNUM = &LASTCC
  SET CMDRESP = NOWHERE
  NGLOBAL HOURS,MINS,DAYNUM,CMDRESP
 /*                                                                  */
 /*  PERFORM THIS CODE AT EVERY INVOCATION                           */
 /*                                                                  */
    %STORAGE
 /*                                                                  */
  SELECT (&DAYNUM)
    WHEN (3) DO
    SYSCALL WEDS
    END
    WHEN (5) DO
    SYSCALL SPACEMAP
    END
    WHEN (6) DO
    SYSCALL SATS
    END
  END
 /*                                                                  */
     SELECT (&HOURS)
      WHEN (6) DO
        SELECT (&MINS)
         WHEN (30:44) DO
                      %SYSDA
                      END
        END
      END
      WHEN (10) DO
        SELECT (&MINS)
         WHEN (15:29) DO
                      /* NOT SATURDAYS (TOO BUSY)                    */
                      IF &DAYNUM EQ 6 THEN EXIT CODE(0)
                      OSCMD F HSM,FREEVOL ML1BACKUPVERSIONS
                      END
        END
      END
      WHEN (18) DO
        SELECT (&MINS)
         WHEN (15:29) DO
                       %$CO
                      END
        END
      END
      WHEN (23) DO
        SELECT (&MINS)
         WHEN (30:44) DO
                      OSCMD S TSSORDR,MBR=FLEXJ01
                      END
        END
      END

  END

     SELECT (&MINS)
      WHEN (00:14) DO
                   /* WRITE FLEX CACHE STATISTICS TO A FILE       */
                   %CACHE
                   END
     END
                      /* END OF PROCESSING   */
  EXIT CODE(0)
                      /* WEDNESDAYS                                  */
WEDS: PROC 0
     SELECT (&HOURS)
      WHEN (18) DO
        SELECT (&MINS)
         WHEN (00:14) DO
                         OSCMD F LLA,REFRESH
                      END
        END
      END
     END
  RETURN CODE(0)
  END
                      /* SATURDAYS ONLY                              */
SATS: PROC 0
     SELECT (&HOURS)
      WHEN (6) DO
        SELECT (&MINS)
         WHEN (00:14) DO
                      OSCMD F HSM,BACKVOL CDS
                      END
         WHEN (15:29) DO
                       OSCMD F HSM,EXPIREBV EXECUTE +
                       NONSMSVERSIONS(DELETEIFBACKEDUP +
                       CATALOGEDDATA(365)  +
                       UNCATALOGEDDATA(100))
                      END
        END
      END
      /* THIS CODE DUMMIED OUT BY FALSE HOUR (16)            */
     END
  RETURN CODE(0)
  END
 /*                                                                  */
SPACEMAP: PROC 0
        SELECT (&MINS)
         WHEN (15:29) DO
                      OSCMD S TSSORDR,MBR=DISKMAPS
                      END
        END
  RETURN CODE(0)
  END
 /*                                                                  */
 /*                                                                  */
 /*                                                                  */
BUGS:  +
       EXIT CODE(8)
